ProMED-mail
e-mail: <promed@usa.healthnet.org>
[Where to begin? First, I took some liberties while editing this report. I
did not alter the quotes but I took some educated guesses as to what was
meant by some of the text. I hope I have not made it worse. Second, if
any country is looking to another country as the source of a hantavirus,
they may be looking in the wrong place. Hard to believe that an invasion
of rodents would make a hantavirus-free country an infected country.
Indeed, I think this is simply silly and wasteful of time and resources. I
have utmost confidence in Dra. Aracely Alava. If she says a specimen does
not contain antibody to a hantavirus, that's good enough for me. However,
laboratories only receive specimens after the fact. What is needed is
education in a calm environment -- prevention-- not hysteria. -- Mod CHC]
